lds\":{\"address\":\"<h2>The Gathering Place Warehouse<\\/h2><p><strong>Shop our fabulous home furnishings warehouse sale on Saturday, February 14th from 9am-2pm and Sunday, February 15th from 10am-12pm. Select items are 50% off! Cash or credit card only.<\\/strong><\\/p><p><strong><br><\\/strong><\\/p>\"}},\"new2\":{\"type\":\"email\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"emailLink\":\"<p><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.flickr.com\\/photos\\/thegatheringplaceoh\\/sets\\/72157650497466462\\/\\\">Click Here<\\/a> <strong>to see some of the items we have for sale.<\\/strong><span><\\/span><\\/p>\"}},\"new3\":{\"type\":\"generalInfo\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"address\":\"<p>The Gathering Place Warehouse Home Furnishings Sale has beautiful furniture at great prices for that empty space in your home. Items include custom furniture, household goods and costume jewelry. Proceeds support the free programs and services at The Gathering Place for individuals and families touched by cancer.<\\/p><p>Please email Cheryl Apisdorf at <a href=\\\"mailto:apisdorf@touchedbycancer.org\\\">apisdorf@touchedbycancer.org<\\/a> to be added to the email list to be notified of upcoming warehouse sales.<\\/p>\"}},\"new4\":{\"type\":\"generalInfo\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"address\":\"<p><strong>HOW TO DONATE TO THE GATHERING PLACE WAREHOUSE<\\/strong><\\/p><p>We accept gently used furniture and other household items which will be sold through our warehouse at 4911 Commerce Parkway in Warrensville Heights (a quarter mile east of Richmond off of Miles Road - directions further down on this page).<\\/p><p>To arrange for someone to come and look at items you would like to donate to our warehouse, or to be notified of future warehouse sales, please contact Cheryl Apisdorf at <a href=\\\"mailto:apisdorf@touchedbycancer.org\\\">apisdorf@touchedbycancer.org<\\/a> or (216) 595-9546.<\\/p><p><strong>Please note that we do not accept drop off donations of furniture or household items at The Gathering Place or at our warehouse.<\\/strong><\\/p>\"}},\"new5\":{\"type\":\"generalInfo\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"address\":\"<p><strong>DIRECTIONS<\\/strong><\\/p><p><br>Please be aware that the warehouse is <strong>not<\\/strong> in Beachwood. The warehouse is located at 4911 Commerce Parkway in Warrensville Heights.<\\/p><p>From the intersection of Chagrin and Richmond, head south on Richmond, make a left turn on Miles Road and Commerce Parkway is the second street on your left. We are in the back of the second last building on the right hand side of the street.<\\/p>\"}}}}}','2015-02-19 19:09:59','2015-02-19 19:09:59','aa727e6d-0c6a-4bd1-bcf5-5ed058b652fb'),(60,70,13,5,'en_us',1,'','{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"5\",\"title\":\"index\",\"slug\":\"index\",\"postDate\":1424373868,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":[]}','2015-02-19 19:24:28','2015-02-19 19:24:28','f89b9b90-b49b-466e-b160-e8005da8e75a'),(61,70,13,5,'en_us',2,'','{\"typeId\":\"15\",\"authorId\":\"5\",\"title\":\"index\",\"slug\":\"index\",\"postDate\":1424373840,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"89\":{\"new1\":{\"type\":\"generalInfo\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"address\":\"<h2>Matching Donations<\\/h2><p>\\r\\n\\tThousands of companies through the United States match donations that their employees make to non-profit organizations. Do you know if your company matches donations?\\r\\n<\\/p><p>\\r\\n\\t<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.matchinggifts.com\\/thegatheringplace\\/\\\" target=\\\"_new\\\">Click here<\\/a> to search a national database of companies who match donations. Search results include information on how to submit for the matching donations and limits on the amount a company will match.\\r\\n<\\/p><p>\\r\\n\\tYou can submit for any of the donations you have made to The Gathering Place including gifts to our Annual Fund, Race for the Place, and tribute gifts made in honor, in celebration and in memory.\\r\\n<\\/p><p>\\r\\n\\tThank you for helping us to double the impact of your donation.\\r\\n<\\/p>\"}},\"new2\":{\"type\":\"generalInfo\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"address\":\"<h2>United Way &amp; The Combined Federal Campaign<\\/h2><p>Are you a donor to The United Way or The Combined Federal Campaign? If so, consider donating a portion of your contribution to The Gathering Place.<\\/p><p>Donors who give $100 or more to United Way are allowed to designate up to 50% of their gift to any registered 501(c) organization. <b>There is no required code number, you simply need to list \\\"The Gathering Place, Beachwood, OH\\\" on the pledge card in the area where you can choose to designate your gift.<\\/b><\\/p><p><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.kintera.org\\/site\\/c.gpIOKZOxFoG\\/b.5573107\\/k.2BFB\\/Donate_Now\\/apps\\/ka\\/sd\\/donorcustom.asp?kntaw38991=C411A719C82A4D56BA1C0C9E0612800C\\\" target=\\\"_new\\\">Click here<\\/a> to make your United Way donation online. Scroll all the way to the bottom and click on \\\"View Investment Areas\\\" to reveal the field where you can enter \\\"The Gathering Place, Beachwood\\\"<b> <\\/b>and the percentage of your donation you would like to designate to The Gathering Place.<\\/p><p>Donors who give to the Combined Federal Campaign are allowed to designate their entire gift to any of the organizations listed in the Combined Federal Campaign Directory. <strong>To designate to The Gathering Place, please use our CFC ID# 71814<\\/strong>.<\\/p><p>Thank you for supporting our community and for helping us to achieve our mission.<\\/p><p>For questions, please contact Beth Darmstadter, Chief Development Officer at <a href=\\\"mailto:darmstadter@touchedbycancer.org\\\">darmstadter@touchedbycancer.org<\\/a>.<\\/p>\"}},\"new3\":{\"type\":\"generalInfo\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"address\":\"<h2>Tributes To Loved Ones<\\/h2><p>Gifts in honor of life-cycle events of loved ones, including birthdays, anniversaries, and wishes for speedy recoveries, as well as memorial giving, provide an opportunity to acknowledge those meaningful times. When special life cycle events occur, please consider making contributions to The Gathering Place. We will promptly acknowledge the requested individual, family or organization.<\\/p><p>There are a number of opportunities at The Gathering Place to acknowledge the special people and events in your life. Following are special contributions that allow for attribution in our facility.<\\/p><p><strong>Library Funds<\\/strong><br>The Mt. Sinai Community Partners Education Center and Lending Library is a vital asset in our programs and services. For one-time gifts of at least $500, a plaque can be added to our donor wall in the library.<\\/p><p><strong>Pond of Life<\\/strong><br>In our healing garden, there is a sculpture of a glass pond which hangs on the wall. \\\"Floating\\\" in this pond are glass lily pads with names of people and groups who have had a significant impact on our community. These lily pads can be purchased for $1,200.<\\/p><p><strong>Celebration of Life Funds<\\/strong><br>Through a minimum donation of $5,000, our Celebration of Life funds are designed to grow over time via continued donations. Due to the nature of their perpetuity, these funds are an excellent way of acknowledging life cycle events forever. A plaque hangs in our indoor garden acknowledging the following special people.<\\/p><p><strong>Brick Pavers<\\/strong><br><a title=\\\"Click here\\\" href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.touchedbycancer.org\\/pavetheway\\/\\\">Click here<\\/a> for more information about purchasing at brick pavers at both locations of The Gathering Place.<\\/p><p><strong>Tribute Cards<\\/strong><br>Tribute Cards are also available for purchase. These cards, which come in packs of five, sell for $50 and allow you to make a tribute gift and include your own note. If you would like to purchase these cards, please come and see Ben, Maureen, or Sue at The Gathering Place.<\\/p><p>For more information, or to make a Tribute Contribution, please click on the \\\"Donate Online\\\" button at the top of the page or contact our Chief Development Officer, Beth Darmstadter at 216.595.9546 or <a href=\\\"mailto:darmstadter@touchedbycancer.org\\\">darmstadter@touchedbycancer.org<\\/a>.<\\/p>\"}},\"new4\":{\"type\":\"generalInfo\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"address\":\"<h2>Community Based Fundraisers<\\/h2><p>The Gathering Place is regularly approached by people in the community who would like to raise money to support our mission. In addition to the money we receive, each of these events also introduces new people to The Gathering Place. We are very appreciative of all the individuals and organizations who help to make these events possible. Visit the<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.touchedbycancer.org\\/2014\\/11\\/7465\\/\\\"> <strong>Celebrating Our Caring Community<\\/strong><\\/a> page, which recognizes those who supported our free programs and services last quarter. If you would like to host\\/organize a fund raising event contact <a href=\\\"mailto:darmstadter@touchedbycancer.org\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\"><strong>Beth Darmstadter<\\/strong><\\/a><a href=\\\"mailto: pagsuyoin@touchedbycancer.org\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\"><strong> <\\/strong><\\/a>or call (216) 595-9546. <\\/p>\"}},\"new5\":{\"type\":\"generalInfo\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"address\":\"<h2>Planned Giving<\\/h2><p><strong><br>Help The Gathering Place thrive through Planned Giving<\\/strong><\\/p><p>Acheive your financial goals while helping secure the future of your family and The Gathering Place.<\\/p><p>Through your Planned Gift to The Gathering Place you will have the satisfaction of knowing that you have enhanced the quality of life for those touched by cancer. You are helping to ensure that programs and services will be provided at no cost for generations to come.<\\/p><p>The benefits of a Planned Gift are:<\\/p><ul><li>Fulfill your commitment to provide quality of life to those touched by cancer<\\/li><li>Create a tax-efficient way to complement your overall financial plan<\\/li><li>Be acknowledged in perpetuity as a member of the Evergreen Society<\\/li><\\/ul><p><strong>Join our Evergreen Society<\\/strong><\\/p><p>As an expression of our gratitude for your support, we invite you to accept a lifetime membership in our Evergreen Society. As a member, you will receive public recognition on a special plaque, a listing in our Annual Report and select newsletters, as well as invitations to special Evergreen Society events.<\\/p><p>Planned Giving can be an effective means of providing for you and your<br>family, as well as benefiting The Gathering Place. We invite you to<br>become part of the tradition of giving that sustains The Gathering<br>Place. You will join a distinguished group of donors who enjoy the<br>satisfaction of knowing they have enhanced the quality of life for<br>those touched by cancer.<\\/p><p>Please contact our Beth Darmstadter, Chief Development Officer, at <a href=\\\"mailto:darmstadter@touchedbycancer.org\\\">darmstadter@touchedbycancer.org<\\/a> to discuss additional options.<\\/p>\"}}}}}','2015-02-19 19:30:23','2015-02-19 19:30:23','6aafdc08-df61-431a-94d7-db2c5738f0b7'),(62,76,14,5,'en_us',1,'','{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"5\",\"title\":\"index\",\"slug\":\"index\",\"postDate\":1424374868,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":[]}','2015-02-19 19:41:08','2015-02-19 19:41:08','55aa2d4c-ded0-472e-bb08-28cc5d77b094'),(63,76,14,5,'en_us',2,'','{\"typeId\":\"16\",\"authorId\":\"5\",\"title\":\"index\",\"slug\":\"index\",\"postDate\":1424374860,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"89\":{\"new1\":{\"type\":\"generalInfo\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"address\":\"<h2>Volunteer With Us<\\/h2><p>Volunteers are an integral part of our community, contributing to our success through their support, dedication and experience.<\\/p><p>Volunteers work with our participants in our Education Center, our children\'s programs and as greeters in our reception area. They also assist with clerical responsibilities, help tend Norma\'s Garden, help coordinate special events, attend health fairs, present information to community groups about The Gathering Place and work at<strong><a title=\\\"The Gathering Place Warehouse\\\" href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.touchedbycancer.org\\/support-us\\/the-gathering-place-warehouse\\/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">The Gathering Place Warehouse<\\/a><\\/strong>.<\\/p><p>To volunteer at the <em>Westlake<\\/em> location, contact Lynn Lubben, Operations &amp; Volunteer Coordinator in Westlake, at <a href=\\\"mailto:lubben@touchedbycancer.org\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">lubben@touchedbycancer.org<\\/a> or call 216-595-9546*.<\\/p><p>To volunteer at our <em>Beachwood<\\/em> location, contact Liz Krantz, Volunteer Coordinator in Beachwood, at <a href=\\\"mailto:krantz@touchedbycancer.org\\\">krantz@touchedbycancer.org<\\/a> or call 216 595-9546*<\\/p>\"}},\"new2\":{\"type\":\"generalInfo\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"address\":\"<p><strong>Volunteer Story<\\/strong><\\/p><p><strong><\\/strong><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.touchedbycancer.org\\/support-us\\/our-volunteers\\/\\\">read story<\\/a><\\/p>\"}},\"new3\":{\"type\":\"generalInfo\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"address\":\"<p>Resource Name<\\/p><p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua.<\\/p><p><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.touchedbycancer.org\\/support-us\\/our-volunteers\\/\\\">read more<\\/a> <\\/p>\"}},\"new4\":{\"type\":\"generalInfo\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"address\":\"<h3>VOLUNTEER POSITIONS<\\/h3><p><strong><em data-redactor-tag=\\\"em\\\">Indirect Services:<\\/em><\\/strong><\\/p><p><strong>1. Special Events<\\/strong>:<\\/p><span class=\\\"wpcf7-form-control-wrap SpecialEvents\\\"><span class=\\\"wpcf7-form-control wpcf7-checkbox\\\" data-redactor-class=\\\"wpcf7-form-control wpcf7-checkbox\\\"> <span class=\\\"wpcf7-list-item-label\\\">Race for the Place-help with our annual run\\/walk to celebrate National Cancer Survivorship (April-early June)<\\/span><\\/span> <span class=\\\"wpcf7-list-item-label\\\">Helping with one day special events (as needed)<\\/span><\\/span> <span class=\\\"wpcf7-list-item-label\\\">Supply baked goods or other refreshments for special programs (as needed)<\\/span><p><strong>2. The Gathering Place Home Furnishings Warehouse<\\/strong><\\/p><p><span class=\\\"wpcf7-form-control-wrap HomeFurnishings\\\"><span class=\\\"wpcf7-form-control wpcf7-checkbox\\\" data-redactor-class=\\\"wpcf7-form-control wpcf7-checkbox\\\"> <span class=\\\"wpcf7-list-item-label\\\">Assist with sales of donated fine household items at our Warrensville Heights Warehouse (as needed)<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p><p><strong>3. Miscellaneous<br><\\/strong><\\/p><p><span class=\\\"wpcf7-form-control-wrap Misc\\\"><span class=\\\"wpcf7-form-control wpcf7-checkbox\\\" data-redactor-class=\\\"wpcf7-form-control wpcf7-checkbox\\\"> <span class=\\\"wpcf7-list-item-label\\\">Clerical help (as needed) <\\/span><\\/span> <span class=\\\"wpcf7-list-item-label\\\">Data Entry (as needed)<\\/span><\\/span> <span class=\\\"wpcf7-list-item-label\\\">Garden weeding and watering (May-September; east location only)<\\/span><br>Other skills you offer:<br><\\/p><p><strong><em data-redactor-tag=\\\"em\\\">Direct Services:<\\/em><\\/strong><\\/p><p>* <strong><u data-redactor-tag=\\\"u\\\">The following volunteer positions require a training session and a personal<\\/u><\\/strong><u> <strong data-redactor-tag=\\\"strong\\\">interview<\\/strong><\\/u><\\/p><p>1. * <strong>Greeter:<\\/strong> <span class=\\\"qualifier\\\">(Adults 18 years or older)<\\/span><\\/p><p><span class=\\\"wpcf7-form-control-wrap Greeter\\\"><span class=\\\"wpcf7-form-control wpcf7-checkbox\\\" data-redactor-class=\\\"wpcf7-form-control wpcf7-checkbox\\\"> <span class=\\\"wpcf7-list-item-label\\\">Responsibilities include answering phones and transferring calls, greeting visitors and giving tours of our facility, registering participants for programs and services, performing some administrative and clerical tasks (must be comfortable multi-tasking and interacting with various types of people including those in crisis). Weekly commitment required for 2-3 hour shift.<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p><p>2. <strong>* Children\'s Program: <\\/strong><span class=\\\"qualifier\\\">(Adult volunteers 18 years or older will need to complete our background check).<\\/span><\\/p><p><span class=\\\"wpcf7-form-control-wrap ChildProgram\\\"><span class=\\\"wpcf7-form-control wpcf7-checkbox\\\" data-redactor-class=\\\"wpcf7-form-control wpcf7-checkbox\\\"> <span class=\\\"wpcf7-list-item-label\\\">Assist child specialists in the various children\'s programs (Adults 18 years or older)<\\/span><\\/span> <span class=\\\"wpcf7-list-item-label\\\">Playroom supervision (14 years or older)<\\/span><\\/span> <span class=\\\"wpcf7-list-item-label\\\">Work alongside staff in our summer animal camp for children (18 years or older \\u2013 requires a week-long commitment)<\\/span><\\/p><p><strong>3. * Outreach: <\\/strong><span class=\\\"qualifier\\\">(Adults 18 years or older)<\\/span><\\/p><p><span class=\\\"wpcf7-form-control-wrap Outreach\\\"><span class=\\\"wpcf7-form-control wpcf7-checkbox\\\" data-redactor-class=\\\"wpcf7-form-control wpcf7-checkbox\\\"> <span class=\\\"wpcf7-list-item-label\\\">Represent the organization by distributing and sharing information about our programs and services at community events, health fairs, etc. Responsibilities include picking up and returning outreach materials at The Gathering Place, driving to various locations east and\\/or west of Cleveland, setting up outreach display and interacting with various types of people.<\\/span><\\/span> <span class=\\\"wpcf7-list-item-label\\\">Community or Physician Ambassador \\u2013 Responsibilities include picking up and delivering Gathering Place materials quarterly to assigned locations in various communities.<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p><p><strong>4. * Education Center\\/Library:<\\/strong> <span class=\\\"qualifier\\\">(Adults 18 years or older)<\\/span><\\/p><p><span class=\\\"wpcf7-form-control-wrap EducationCenter\\\"><span class=\\\"wpcf7-form-control wpcf7-checkbox\\\" data-redactor-class=\\\"wpcf7-form-control wpcf7-checkbox\\\"> <span class=\\\"wpcf7-list-item-label\\\">Assist participants in their search for information (must be comfortable using the computer and have good interpersonal skills).<\\/span><\\/span> <span class=\\\"wpcf7-list-item-label\\\">Perform administrative and clerical tasks as needed by our medical librarian.<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p><p><strong>5. * Breast Cancer Connection <\\/strong><span class=\\\"qualifier\\\">(for breast cancer survivors)<\\/span><\\/p><p><span class=\\\"wpcf7-form-control-wrap BreastCancer\\\"><span class=\\\"wpcf7-form-control wpcf7-checkbox\\\" data-redactor-class=\\\"wpcf7-form-control wpcf7-checkbox\\\"> <span class=\\\"wpcf7-list-item-label\\\">Provide phone support to participants who are newly diagnosed with breast cancer.<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p><p><strong>6. * Healing Arts <\\/strong><span class=\\\"qualifier\\\">(females only \\u2013 21 years or older with at least one year of experience; background check and references required)<\\/span><\\/p><p><span class=\\\"wpcf7-form-control-wrap HealingArts\\\"><span class=\\\"wpcf7-form-control wpcf7-checkbox\\\" data-redactor-class=\\\"wpcf7-form-control wpcf7-checkbox\\\"> <span class=\\\"wpcf7-list-item-label\\\">Reiki Master <\\/span><\\/span> <span class=\\\"wpcf7-list-item-label\\\">Licensed Massage Therapist<\\/span><\\/span> <span class=\\\"wpcf7-list-item-label\\\">Certified Reflexologist<\\/span><\\/p><p>Previous volunteer experience:<\\/p><p>How did you hear about The Gathering Place?<\\/p><p>Cancer survivor? (optional)<span class=\\\"wpcf7-form-control-wrap Survivor\\\"><span class=\\\"wpcf7-form-control wpcf7-radio\